article.headline: Delaware St. 61, Md.-Eastern Shore 47
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Jahsha Bluntt scored 14 points and Delaware State defeated Maryland-Eastern Shore 61-47 Monday. Darrin Shine had 11 points on 5-of-9 shooting for the Hornets (8-9, 5-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). The Hawks (2-14, 0-5 MEAC) had three players in double figures led by Corey Brown, who came off the bench to score 17 points. Ed Tyson had 14 points and Antonio McMillion added 11. The score was tied 34-34 at halftime, but Delaware State started the second half with an 11-0 run and UMES couldn't get closer than 8 after a Tyson lay-up with 13:25 remaining.
